entries.title: Jan. 6 rioter who assaulted Capitol Police Officer Brian Sicknick sentenced to over 6 years in jail
entries.description: A man who assaulted United States Capitol Police Officer Brian Sicknick with pepper spray on January 6, 2021, was sentenced on Friday to 80 months behind bars.

entries.title: Record rainfall hits New Zealand's largest city. See what it did to the airport
entries.description: Torrential rainfall battered Auckland, New Zealand, causing major flooding and numerous evacuations. The country's largest city declared a state of emergency and was forced to close its airport.

entries.title: Five dead and several injured after shooting in Jerusalem, says Israeli Emergency Services
entries.description: Five people were killed and several were injured during a shooting in Jerusalem, Israel's Magen David Adom (MDA) emergency rescue services said Friday.

entries.title: Pamela Anderson defends Tim Allen after flashing allegation
entries.description: Pamela Anderson is addressing discussion about a story regarding her "Home Improvement" costar Tim Allen that is part of her new memoir, "Love Pamela."

entries.title: A Russian cemetery used for the mercenary group's deceased fighters is rapidly expanding amid heavy losses in eastern Ukraine
Tyre Nichols' family speaks before expected release of videos from his arrest
entries.description: • Exclusive: 'You're going to see acts that defy humanity,' police chief says

entries.title: Inside Air France's new business class cabin
entries.description: Air France has just launched a plush new long-haul business cabin on one of its Boeing 777-200ER planes complete with sliding doors and redesigned seats.

entries.title: Archaeologists may have found Egypt's oldest mummy
entries.description: Archeologists have uncovered what may be the oldest mummy ever found in Egypt.

entries.title: Video of attack on Paul Pelosi released
entries.description: San Francisco Superior Court on Friday released video and audio recorded during last year's attack on Paul Pelosi after a California court ruled the district attorney's office must make the materials public.

entries.title: Officials: Ukraine facing 'permanent' assault in the east
US Supreme Court did not disclose financial relationship with expert brought in to review leak probe
entries.description: The Supreme Court did not disclose its longstanding financial ties with former Homeland Security Secretary Michael Chertoff even as it touted him as an expert who independently validated its investigation into who leaked the draft opinion overturning Roe v. Wade.

entries.title: British teenager who made far-right hate videos 'influencing' Buffalo shooter jailed for 11 years
entries.description: A British teenager who made far-right extremist videos that "influenced" the mass shooter who killed 10 Black people in a Buffalo, New York, supermarket was jailed for 11 and a half years Friday, the UK's PA  Medis news agency reported.

entries.title: German parliament officially commemorates LGBTQ victims of Nazi regime for first time
entries.description: The German parliament for the first time on Friday focused its annual Holocaust memorial commemorations on people persecuted and killed over their sexual or gender identity during World War II.

entries.title: Deaths in pregnant or recently pregnant women have risen, especially for unrelated causes such as drug poisoning and homicide
entries.description: The mortality rate of pregnant and recently pregnant women in the United States rose almost 30% between 2019 and 2020, according to a new study.

entries.title: Gun attack on Azerbaijan embassy in Tehran kills security chief
entries.description: A gunman entered Azerbaijan's embassy in the Iranian capital and killed one person on Friday, the foreign ministries of Iran and Azerbaijan confirmed in separate statements, with both citing different motives for the deadly attack.

entries.title: Tyre Nichols' mom describes nightmare of son's death following his violent arrest
'You're going to see acts that defy humanity,' police chief says, as officials urge calm when Tyre Nichols arrest videos are released publicly tonight
'It Ends With Us' movie casts Blake Lively and Justin Baldoni
entries.description: BookTok is all abuzz with the news that Blake Lively and Justin Baldoni will be starring in a movie based on the bestselling romance novel, "It Ends With Us."

entries.title: Biden formally announces Ron Klain is stepping down as White House chief of staff and will be replaced by Jeff Zients
entries.description: President Joe Biden announced White House chief of staff Ron Klain will step down next week and will be replaced by Jeff Zients, the former Obama administration official who ran Biden's Covid-19 response operation.

entries.title: US tourist fined for driving rental car over medieval Italian bridge
entries.description: The Ponte Vecchio, a beautiful centuries-old bridge spanning the Arno River in the Italian city of Florence, is best viewed on foot, with crowds of tourists regularly thronging the pedestrianized structure to view its ancient stonework.

entries.title: China's reopening isn't all good news. Inflation could get a second wind
entries.description: China's swift reopening after nearly three years of strict coronavirus controls could provide a much-needed boost to global economic growth, but may also stoke inflation just as it has shown signs of falling back.

entries.title: Watch CNN's full interview with parents of Tyre Nichols and family attorney Ben Crump
entries.description: In their first interview since charges were announced for the officers involved in the violent arrest and subsequent death of their son Tyre Nichols, the 29-year-old's parents sit down with CNN's Don Lemon to discuss what they are going through.

entries.title: 'Shrinking' turns grief into laughter in an Apple TV+ series that really grows on you
entries.description: "Shrinking" starts slowly, feeling like it's going to be just another dour comedy as much about grief as laughs. Stick with it, though, and this Apple TV+ series from the team behind "Ted Lasso" really grows on you, with some very funny writing, appealing characters, and as a nifty bonus, Harrison Ford as an unexpectedly effective sitcom version of a cranky old man.

entries.title: 'Shotgun Wedding' loads up a Jennifer Lopez rom-com that misfires badly
entries.description: Although we're almost past the point of having the stench of death surround movies when they head directly to streaming, that assessment applies to "Shotgun Wedding," which loads both barrels with Jennifer Lopez, late-replacement Josh Duhamel and Jennifer Coolidge and still fires blanks. The movie arrives in the US via Amazon, but even that invitation is worth declining.

entries.title: Alan Cumming returns OBE award in protest at 'toxicity' of British Empire
entries.description: Alan Cumming has returned a prestigious royal award in an effort to sever his association with the "toxicity" of the British Empire.

entries.title: Jay Leno suffers broken bones in motorcycle accident
entries.description: Jay Leno says he broke multiple bones in a motorcycle accident months after suffering severe burns to his face after another mishap.

entries.title: Lawyer shares that Nichols called out for mom 3 times
entries.description: RowVaughn Wells, the mother of Tyre Nichols, discusses Nichols reportedly calling out for her during a deadly beating by Memphis police officers that was captured on video. Police say they will release the video today.

entries.title: 'A war of attrition': Humans and extreme drought damaging Amazon rainforest much more than thought, study suggests
entries.description: Human activity and extreme drought is causing far more damage to the Amazon rainforest than previously thought, exacerbating climate change, according to a new study.

entries.title: 'Disregard for humanity': Memphis Police Chief describes Nichols arrest footage
entries.description: In an exclusive CNN interview, Don Lemon talks to Memphis Police Chief Cerelyn "CJ" Davis about her reaction to the bodycam footage of Tyre Nichols' violent arrest and what prompted her to charge the officers involved.

entries.title: Analysis: Is Prince Andrew planning to revisit his US sex abuse case?
entries.description: You might get a sense of deja vu with this edition of Royal News. Long-time readers will probably recall the scandal that engulfed Britain's royal family this time last year as Prince Andrew faced legal action in the United States over alleged historical sexual abuse.

entries.title: Opinion: This 'magical' substitute for eggs may already be in your kitchen pantry
entries.description: A year ago, we couldn't have imagined people being so fearful of running out of eggs that they'd turn to smuggling cases across the Mexican border or renting chickens with portable coops to keep them in steady supply. But here we are.

entries.title: Complete Roman city uncovered in Luxor, Egypt
entries.description: Archaeologists working in the southern Egyptian city of Luxor have uncovered a complete 1,800-year-old Roman city.

entries.title: She was crying alone at an airport. Then she met her future best friend
entries.description: Maggie Musgrave was sitting, alone, in Miami International Airport, crying.

entries.title: Novak Djokovic through to Australian Open final and on course to equal Rafael Nadal's all-time grand slam record
entries.description: Novak Djokovic remains on course to win a record-equaling 22nd grand slam title after easily beating American Tommy Paul in straight sets in the Australian Open semifinals Friday, setting up a mouthwatering final with Stefanos Tsitsipas.

entries.title: South Africa to send dozens of cheetahs to India under new deal
entries.description: South Africa has signed an agreement with India to reintroduce dozens of cheetahs to the South Asian country after eight of the big cats were sent from neighboring Namibia in 2022.

entries.title: Federal prosecutors discussed charging Trump in Stormy Daniels case when he left office, book says
entries.description: Days before then-President Donald Trump left the White House, federal prosecutors in New York discussed whether to potentially charge Trump with campaign finance crimes once he was out of office, according to a new book from CNN senior legal analyst Elie Honig.

entries.title: Opinion: Why legal abortion may not be safe in blue states
entries.description: Since the Supreme Court reversed Roe v. Wade in June, promising strategies have emerged to protect abortion rights in individual states. Some have begun to pass ballot initiatives to preserve or create state constitutional protection. Others have looked to legislatures to shield doctors and those who help people seeking abortion from potential consequences in conservative states.

entries.title: Gautam Adani's business loses $50 billion in market value
entries.description: The value of Gautam Adani's business empire has crashed by more than $50 billion this week since Hindenburg Research, a US firm that makes money from short selling, published a blistering report accusing it of fraud.

entries.title: Look of the Week: Apple Martin looks every bit the 'Chanel girl'
entries.description: When the late Karl Lagerfeld met Gwyneth Paltrow and Chris Martin's daughter Apple, as a baby, he predicted that she would one day become "a Chanel girl."

entries.title: 'A ginormous can of worms': How a fight over snow crabs could lead to a win for oil drilling access
entries.description: A legal fight in Norway over snow crabs could end up having big implications for access to oil in the Arctic.

entries.title: Carolina Panthers reunite with their first starting quarterback after appointing Frank Reich as head coach
entries.description: The Carolina Panthers have turned to a familiar face in their search for a new head coach.

entries.title: CCTV video shows bus flooded with water after plunging into lake
entries.description: There were no fatalities recorded after the incident which took place in the eastern Turkish city of Malatya, Reuters reports.

entries.title: When NASA tested a plane with a pivoting wing
entries.description: Not many aircraft can claim to be truly one of a kind, but the NASA AD-1 is undoubtedly one of them. A slim pointed cigar with a single wing that pivoted around a central point, which led to a jarring asymmetry in flight. No other piloted plane has ever been built with a wing that could turn to a lopsided 20 to 2 angle -- but the fascinating story is why it did at all.

entries.title: Former Detroit Lions and Los Angeles Chargers linebacker Jessie Lemonier dies aged 25
entries.description: Former Detroit Lions and Los Angeles Chargers linebacker Jessie Lemonier died on Thursday aged 25, according to a statement from the Lions.

entries.title: Trump will hit the trail looking to reinvigorate his campaign
entries.description: Donald Trump's monthslong hiatus from the campaign trail is about to end.

entries.title: New details emerge about the suspect in the Northern California farm shootings that left 7 dead
entries.description: New details have emerged about the farmworker accused of killing several people in Northern California on Monday -- an attack that has stunned the small coastal city of Half Moon Bay amid carnage from other mass shootings in the state over the past week.

entries.title: Russians on Western tanks for Ukraine: 'Our opinions mean diddly-squat'
entries.description: After the announcement of Germany and the US to supply tanks to Ukraine, Russia's propaganda machine is working at full throttle. Russian state TV playing down risks to Russian troops in Ukraine seems to be working on some - but not everyone is buying the hype. CNN's Nic Robertson reports.

entries.title: How family and officials who have seen video of Tyre Nichols' arrest are reacting
entries.description: "Appalling." "Savage." "Inhumane."

entries.title: Quarterbacks in the NFL playoffs are getting younger. Here's why their age is important
entries.description: As British two-tone band The Specials once sang: "You've done too much, much too young."

entries.title: US Marines officially opens first new base in 70 years on island of Guam
entries.description: The United States Marine Corps on Thursday officially opened its first new base in 70 years, a 4,000-acre installation on the US Pacific island of Guam that one day is expected to host 5,000 Marines.

entries.title: China still wants to control Big Tech. It's just pulling different strings
entries.description: Investors have raced back into Chinese tech stocks this year, encouraged by an apparent truce in a two-year battle between some of the country's most powerful regulators and its biggest internet companies.

entries.title: After 3 years of Covid, CNN went deep into rural China for Lunar New Year. Here's what we found and how officials tried stopping us
entries.description: In China's southern Guizhou province, there's a tiny village in the southeast corner, nestled deep within the mountains, called Dali. A wall of lush green trees and bamboo surround this village of about one-thousand people, who've lived in wooden homes with gray-tiled roofs for centuries.

entries.title: See how officials responded to CNN team in rural China
entries.description: CNN's Selina Wang traveled to rural China during the traditional Lunar New Year. See how government officials responded.

entries.title: Ukraine says it shot down most of the missiles and drones launched by Russia on Thursday
Officials call for calm as video footage of Tyre Nichols' arrest will be released publicly Friday night, authorities say
entries.description: After five Memphis police officers were charged on Thursday in the death of Tyre Nichols following a traffic stop earlier this month, authorities say video footage of the encounter will be released to the public late Friday.

entries.title: Video shows clash between students and police over banned BBC documentary
entries.description: At least a dozen Indian university students have been detained by police over plans to screen a banned BBC documentary critical of Prime Minister Narendra Modi, according to the leader of a student group. CNN's Anna Coren has more.

entries.title: Zelensky calls for more Western weapons after latest Russian missile strikes
Peru's embattled president could have eased the crisis. What happened?
entries.description: When Dina Boluarte was anointed Peru's sixth president in five years, she faced battles on two fronts: appeasing the lawmakers who had ousted her boss and predecessor Pedro Castillo, and calming protesterse enraged by the dethroning of yet another president.

entries.title: Eight confirmed dead after ship capsizes near Japan, nine still missing
entries.description: Eight people who were aboard a cargo ship that capsized off the coast of Japan earlier this week have died and nine remain missing, the Japan Coast Guard said Thursday.

entries.title: Five Chinese citizens were killed in Half Moon Bay shooting, consulate says
entries.description: Five of the seven people killed in the Half Moon Bay shootings in California were Chinese citizens, China's consulate in San Francisco said Thursday.

entries.title: Kyiv must tackle training, technical support and supply chain issues in deploying tanks donated by NATO allies to make an impact in its war with Russia
entries.description: Those hoping that main battle tanks donated by NATO allies to Ukraine will have an immediate impact in its war with Russia may have to adjust their expectations.

entries.title: BuzzFeed's CEO says AI could usher in a 'new model for digital media,' but warns against a 'dystopian' path
entries.description: Over the holidays, while most media executives were perhaps looking to get a reprieve from work, Jonah Peretti was online, fully immersed in experimenting with artificial intelligence.

entries.title: Meet the man with the award-winning mustache
entries.description: Bob Baker's mustache has won the national mustache styling championship twice and even landed him a movie role. CNN affiliate WVIR reports.

entries.title: Grand Canyon's Havasu Falls to reopen to visitors after 3-year closure
entries.description: Havasu Falls, one of the most intriguing features of the Grand Canyon system, will be reopening to visitors after a three-year closure caused by the Covid-19 pandemic. But it's with a catch.

entries.title: Ex-boyfriend of George Santos speaks out
entries.description: CNN's Erin Burnett talks to the former boyfriend of embattled Rep. George Santos (R-NY) about their relationship and the many false claims Santos has publicly made.

entries.title: Pakistani rupee plummets as markets adjust to removal of unofficial controls
entries.description: The Pakistani rupee fell 9.6% against the dollar on Thursday, central bank data showed — the biggest one-day drop in over two decades — in a slump that may persuade the International Monetary Fund to resume lending to the country.

entries.title: This bio-designer is creating flavorful future food with microalgae
entries.description: The year is 2050. Agriculture happens in labs, as well as fields. And on the menu for dinner? Microalgae.

entries.title: Retired maj. general predicts where Ukraine's renewed offensive will take place
entries.description: On Thursday, Ukrainian president Volodymyr Zelensky said his government is aware of Russian plans for future operations in Ukraine and indicated that they were working to counter Moscow's moves. Maj. Gen. James "Spider" Marks (Ret.) joins CNN's Wolf Blitzer to discuss the opportunities of Ukraine's renewed offensive as they expect the delivery of western tanks.

entries.title: 'Beauty is power': For Eileen Gu, fashion and sport aren't so different
entries.description: If Eileen Gu's account of last Saturday's Freestyle Ski World Cup event in Calgary is anything to go by, a day in the Olympian's life is as varied as it is busy: She took first place in morning qualifiers, wrote two essays, read some René Descartes and George Berkeley for a philosophy class and then "did some physics" before returning to the slopes for the final.

entries.title: Putin acknowledges problem with Russia's defense industry
entries.description: Russian investigative journalist Andrei Soldatov says that Russian President Vladimir Putin has turned to recruiting convicts to staff military factories that are low on manpower.

entries.title: The Earth's core is changing. What does that mean for us?
entries.description: If a person is said to be grounded, it means that they are sensible and stable -- solid individuals who can be relied upon to give a careful and considered opinion. The very meaning of the term comes from the solidity and stability of the ground on which we walk. However, recent reports in the media have painted a different picture of what goes on beneath the ground -- one in which the core of the Earth is doing some very surprising and unexpected things.

entries.title: CNN reporter calls out Santos on his lie about playing college volleyball
entries.description: CNN's Manu Raju questions embattled Rep. George Santos (R-NY) about his false claim of being on Baruch College's volleyball team.

entries.title: Friend of charged officer describes conversation they had about Nichols' death
entries.description: CNN's Nick Valencia reports on the arrest of 5 Memphis police officers charged in the death of Tyre Nichols and speaks with Bennie Cobb, a family friend of one of the officers.

entries.title: CNN goes to the front lines of major US and Israel joint military exercise
entries.description: CNN gets exclusive access to the largest joint military exercise ever between the US and Israel, sending a clear signal to Iran and underscoring the strength of their alliance. CNN's Hadas Gold reports.
